  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Institutional Links June 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Grants provide seed-funding to initiate new/develop existing research and innovation partnerships between groups/departments/institutions in partner countries and the UK. Grants are flexible and responsive to in-country needs, allowing partners to establish collaborations on areas linked to country priorities and development needs, and to include relevant non-academic partners (including SMEs/ NGOs).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the development and consolidate networks of researchers in the UK and Brazil, favouring an interdisciplinary approach that will use the collection and systematisation of data together with the extensive research on these diseases to create and implement public health methodologies, indicators, and database that will inform, monitor and evaluate public health policies.</narrative>
  </description>
